# Community Problem Reporting System

MERN: MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js. JWT auth. Roles: citizen, admin, authority.

## Architecture (SRS §7)

- Presentation: React SPA (Bootstrap or Tailwind)
- Application: Express REST API, MVC (routes, controllers, models)
- Data: MongoDB + Mongoose

## Core workflow

Citizen submits → Pending Verification → Admin verifies/rejects → Admin assigns Authority → Authority updates status → Citizen notified; statusHistory auditable.

## Entities (SRS §9)

User, Complaint, Notification — see docs/SRS.md for fields and enums.

## API (SRS §10)

Auth, Users, Complaints (citizen/admin/authority), Notifications, Analytics. JWT in Authorization header; RBAC on server for every protected route.

## Security (SRS §12)

bcrypt passwords; JWT expiry ~24h; server-side RBAC; input validation/sanitization; image type/size validation; HTTPS in production.

## Out of scope v1.0

Native apps, payments, GIS pinning, i18n — do not implement.
